        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down. | Bromley. | Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Oct. 18<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Lindley</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I thank you sincerely for your information.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> Your tracing shows that the species is saccatum beyond a doubt.—<ref target="#foot.f3"/> I wrote to Gardener’s Chron. as I thought it would trouble you less to answer in that way.<ref target="#foot.f4"/> I am very much obliged.— I have been extremely much interested with Catasetum, and indeed with many exotic Orchids, which I have been looking at in aid of an opusculus, on the fertilisation of British Orchids. I very much fear that in publishing I am doing a rash act; but Orchids have interested me more than almost anything in my life. Your work shows that you carefully understand this feeling.<ref target="#foot.f5"/></p>
<p>Yours very sincerely &amp; obliged | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
                <div type="tnotes">
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.3 way.] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi></note>
                </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is provided by the reference to the publication of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6010.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Orchids</hi></ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Lindley’s letter has not been found.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><hi rend="italic">Catasetum saccatum</hi> is discussed in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6010.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Orchids</hi></ref>, pp. 214–31.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">Lindley was the editor of the <hi rend="italic">Gardeners’ Chronicle</hi>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">Lindley had a special interest in orchids and was the author or editor of a number of works in which the morphology and taxonomy of orchids was described. CD often cited Lindley’s works in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6010.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Orchids</hi></ref>.</note>
